    <entry>
      <title>Setup maven and maven wrapper in mac</title>
      <link href="2021/02/16/Setup-maven-and-maven-wrapper-in-mac/"/>
      <url>2021/02/16/Setup-maven-and-maven-wrapper-in-mac/</url>
      
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>In Mac, it is suggested to install the latest maven using brew. However, if Mac OS version is too old to support the installation, you have to manually install maven by downloading from <a href="https://maven.apache.org/download.cgi">maven</a>, for example apache-maven-3.6.3-bin.tar.gz</p><ul><li><p>Step 1<br>Go to download folder, and extract the file apache-maven-3.6.3</p></li><li><p>Step 2<br>Setup maven classpath to your env variable by adding the following three lines into .bash_profile file.</p><figure class="highlight plain"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">export JAVA_HOME&#x3D;&#x2F;Library&#x2F;Java&#x2F;JavaVirtualMachines&#x2F;jdk-15.0.2.jdk&#x2F;Contents&#x2F;Home</span><br><span class="line">export M2_HOME&#x3D;~&#x2F;apache-maven-3.6.3</span><br><span class="line">export PATH&#x3D;$PATH:$M2_HOME&#x2F;bin</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>Note: make sure the JDK installation.</p></li><li><p>Step 3<br>Reload .bash_profile from the command line</p><figure class="highlight plain"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">source ~&#x2F;.bash_profile</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p>Step 3<br>Verify the maven installation via command mvn -version</p></li><li><p>Step 4<br>Install Maven Wrapper plugin to make auto installation in a simple Spring Boot project.</p><figure class="highlight plain"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">mvn -N io.takari:maven:wrapper</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>Build Spring Boot project by mvnw command</p><figure class="highlight plain"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">.&#x2F;mvnw clean install</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>Run Spring-Boot project by mvnw command</p><figure class="highlight plain"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">.&#x2F;mvnw spring-boot:run</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li></ul>]]></content>
      
      
