      <title>Hibernate logs are not available since v4</title>
      <link href="2020/04/13/Hibernate-logs-are-not-available-since-v4/"/>
      <url>2020/04/13/Hibernate-logs-are-not-available-since-v4/</url>
      
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>Since v4, Hibernate uses jboss-logging as logging framework. This framework delegates to one of the following: log4j2, log4j, slf4j, Java Utils Logging.</p><h2 id="Diagnostics"><a href="#Diagnostics" class="headerlink" title="Diagnostics:"></a>Diagnostics:</h2><p>My application uses SLF4J/Log4j as logging library but jboss-logging can’t seem to find this library. The reason is probably that jboss-logging is loaded from the Weblogic server modules classloader whereas log4j is loaded from the application classloader.</p><h2 id="Solution"><a href="#Solution" class="headerlink" title="Solution:"></a>Solution:</h2><p>Tell Weblogic to use the application-provider jboss-logging instead of the Weblogic-provided one. This is done by having the following in weblogic.xml:</p><figure class="highlight plain"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">&lt;container-descriptor&gt;</span><br><span class="line">  &lt;prefer-application-packages&gt; </span><br><span class="line">    &lt;!-- Weblogic provides its own jboss-logging library which Hibernate uses. Since it&#39;s in the server class-loader (com.oracle.classloader.weblogic.LaunchClassLoader), it doesn&#39;t see the application-provided SLF4J and Log4j libraries. So ask Weblogic to use our jboss-logging. --&gt;</span><br><span class="line">    &lt;package-name&gt;org.jboss.logging&lt;&#x2F;package-name&gt;</span><br><span class="line">  &lt;&#x2F;prefer-application-packages&gt;</span><br><span class="line">&lt;&#x2F;container-descriptor&gt;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p><strong>Note:</strong> Don’t forget to set the Log4j appender threshold to TRACE.</p>]]></content>
      
      
