      <title>Primefaces JS/CSS not loading</title>
      <link href="2020/03/29/Primefaces-JS-CSS-not-loading/"/>
      <url>2020/03/29/Primefaces-JS-CSS-not-loading/</url>
      
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>PrimeFaces will auto-include the necessary JS/CSS resources in <code>&lt;h:head&gt;</code>. However, if you don’t have that tag and use a “plain HTML” <code>&lt;head&gt;</code>, the included JS/CSS will not be loaded.</p><p>This mistake should also have been logged in the server log as below:<br><em>One or more resources has the target of ‘head’ but not ‘head’ component has been defined within the view</em></p><h2 id="Solution"><a href="#Solution" class="headerlink" title="Solution:"></a>Solution:</h2><p>Put JS/CSS resources in <code>&lt;h:head&gt;</code> as follows.</p><figure class="highlight plain"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br><span class="line">8</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">&lt;html&gt;</span><br><span class="line">    &lt;h:head&gt;</span><br><span class="line">        ...</span><br><span class="line">    &lt;&#x2F;h:head&gt;</span><br><span class="line">    &lt;h:body&gt;</span><br><span class="line">        ...</span><br><span class="line">    &lt;&#x2F;h:body&gt;</span><br><span class="line">&lt;&#x2F;html&gt;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>]]></content>
      
      
