      <link href="2020/03/28/redirect-if-javascript-not-support-in-browser/"/>
      <url>2020/03/28/redirect-if-javascript-not-support-in-browser/</url>
      
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>The <code>&lt;noscript&gt;</code> tag defines an alternate content for users that have disabled scripts in their browser or have a browser that doesn’t support script.</p><p>The <code>&lt;noscript&gt;</code> element can be used in both <code>&lt;head&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;body&gt;</code>.</p><p>When used inside the <code>&lt;head&gt;</code> element: <code>&lt;noscript&gt;</code> must contain only <code>&lt;link&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;style&gt;</code>, and <code>&lt;meta&gt;</code> elements.</p><p>The content inside the <code>&lt;noscript&gt;</code> element will be displayed if scripts are not supported, or are disabled in the user’s browser.</p><p>Example:</p><figure class="highlight plain"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">&lt;noscript&gt;</span><br><span class="line">    &lt;meta http-equiv&#x3D;&quot;REFRESH&quot; content&#x3D;&quot;0;url&#x3D;&#x2F;fuelwatch&#x2F;pages&#x2F;javascriptBlockedRedirect.jspx&quot; &#x2F;&gt;</span><br><span class="line">&lt;&#x2F;noscript&gt;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>]]></content>
      
      
